    <div id="School-Day" class="content-section">
      <h1>Day Routine</h1>
      <p>Learn about our daily routine and caring activities for creche children.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Arrival & Welcome:</strong> 7:30am – 8:00am. Little ones are greeted, settled, and introduced to a calm start.</li>
        <li><strong>Sensory Time:</strong> 8:00am – 8:30am. Gentle songs, soft storytelling, and sensory play to soothe and engage.</li>
        <li><strong>Guided Play:</strong> 8:30am – 10:00am. Age-appropriate activities focused on motor skills, textures, and early language.</li>
        <li><strong>Snack & Rest:</strong> 10:00am – 10:45am. Healthy snacks followed by quiet rest or nap time in a comfortable setting.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Moments:</strong> 10:45am – 12:00pm. Simple art, finger painting, and music for gentle self-expression.</li>
        <li><strong>Lunch & Relaxation:</strong> 12:00pm – 1:30pm. Nutritious meals and calm time for digestion and comfort.</li>
        <li><strong>Afternoon Care:</strong> 1:30pm – 2:30pm. Story time, cuddles, and parent communication to prepare for pickup.</li>
        <li><strong>Pick-Up:</strong> 2:30pm – 3:00pm. Children leave with a summary of the day and any parent updates.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/successful-schoolgirl_1098-13593.avif" alt="Creche Activities" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
    </div>

    <div id="Curriculum" class="content-section">
      <h1>Curriculum</h1>
      <p>Explore our comprehensive curriculum designed for young learners.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Language & Literacy:</strong> Early reading, storytelling, and communication skills.</li>
        <li><strong>Numeracy:</strong> Introduction to numbers, shapes, and patterns through fun activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Science & Discovery:</strong> Exploring the world with simple experiments and nature walks.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Arts:</strong> Drawing, painting, music, and movement to inspire imagination.</li>
        <li><strong>Social & Emotional Learning:</strong> Building friendships, empathy, and confidence.</li>
        <li><strong>Faith & Values:</strong> Instilling Christian values and character development.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/other-uniform.webp" alt="Creche Curriculum" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
